    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36a.41"/>
                
                <note><hi rend="caps">C O P Y</hi></note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">41</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Santiniketan
                        4-9-72
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I have <hi rend="underline">no</hi> excuse for not writing to you during this long one decade. But I know you will be ready to excuse the remissness. You have not been absent from my thoughts. No, sir! How I had looked forward to the visit! Well, the meeting of minds is in material<sic>immaterial</sic>. There are modes of communication that our communication systems know not of.</p> 
                
                <p>Sometime back I had reports of one of your <hi rend="caps">T.V.</hi> interviews and how your book of poems is selling still. They will sell when The Waste Land<sic>Wasteland</sic> and other connoisseurs of chaos are forgotten!</p> 
                
                <p>Let me give you one or two information about what I've been doing. I have barged into the Encyclopaedia Britanica<sic>Britannica</sic> Fraternity. In brief, the next edition will have an article by me on mysticism. I have published a little. One of these will be on its way to you in another fortnight or so; on the poetry of _____ _______. A travelogue called _____________, has been sent a few days back. I should have done this years back. It contains two pieces on you. In fact, one is by you, you'll see. But the main thing is that I feel terribly drawn to the inner life, not by neglecting the outer. You know what I mean. Contemplations of the world mite! <note>(?)</note></p>
                
                <p>Anything you care to write -- or dictate -- will be welcome.</p>
                
                <p>With a thousand <hi rend="underline">salaams</hi> to an elder of the tribe, who has meant so much to me.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours</salute>
                    
                    <note>(?)</note> <signed>Soeir</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <p>What about sending a poem or two - and a recent photograph?</p> 
                </postscript>
                
                <fw>2</fw>
                
            </div1>
            
            
